The following is what I sent to Riot in a support ticket:

"Hello, recently while I was in champion select I got kicked with a notification stating that I had been given a 14-day ban for intentionally feeding. The notification linked the list of &quot;games&quot; in which I was allegedly intentionally feeding. There was only one game, the last game that I played in fact. Here is the link to that particular match:

 http://matchhistory.na.leagueoflegends.com/en/#match-details/NA1/2016447304/201849748?tab=overview. 

With a closer inspection of this particular match, you may notice that I was the only person that got any objectives at all (all of which were in my lane). I managed to push all of the way to their nexus turrets. The first fight that I attempted bot lane ended in a miserable loss. They killed me and my lane partner while we didn&#039;t kill anyone. This season snowballing is very extreme with most games ending before the 25 minute mark. As me and my partner were both melee champs against a ranged support and marksman we quickly were decimated whenever we attempted to touch a creep. We decided that this strategy wasn&#039;t going to work. We would just simply get no minion kills and lose all of our turrets in lane, so we decided to win by irregular means. If you manage to look past your automated ban system (which is heavily flawed if I do say so myself), you will see that I wasn&#039;t intentionally feeding or mindlessly running into the enemy team on purpose like players I so often have the privilege of playing with (who never get banned) , but I was trying to win the game by gaining objectives. 

I tried to change the meta and see if something else besides the norm would be a greater way to win the game, and I was unsuccessful. With this failure I was rewarded with a 14-day account suspension. I tried to use my innovation and see if there was another way to win the game and I received a cold slap in the face. I also want to highlight the fact that the list of &quot;games&quot; only had one game. Just one. I would understand if there were several games in which I was flagged for feeding. But just a single one. Everyone has bad games. And I had a terrible game in which I tried to turn into a win. 

Intentionally feeding is when one runs around a turret, afks, and lets the enemy kill them. If you review this match, you will see that I never once did that. I may have died whilst killing a turret or two, but I was trying to win the game. As I am always constantly reminded in ranked games, &quot;Turrets win games, not kills&quot;. I didn&#039;t &quot;troll in pre-lobby&quot;, I didn&#039;t cry because I didn&#039;t get the lane I wanted. I planned to play Yi bot and go &quot;double rageblade daddy push mode&quot; with my friend. I would also like to state that this was a normal match, so I figured I could try to go outside of the boring meta a little bit, knowing that a failure would result in literally no loss as I would still get IP and no one would lose MMR for ranked queues. I am not an intentional feeder, and I was hurt by this statement accusing me of the sort: &quot;Your deliberate choice to ruin League for others reflects a gross breach of community-defined standards&quot;. 

I never in my wildest dreams would want to &quot;ruin League for others&quot; as I know what it feels like as it happens to me frequently in RANKED. I know what it feels like to plead with someone to just play the game and not intentionally feed, I would never ruin everyone else&#039;s experience by doing that. It is my hope and plea that you will review this case and find that I wasn&#039;t &quot;intentionally feeding&quot;. An automated suspension system can only go off of pre-entered algorithms and programs. I want a real human being to look this case over. Thank you for the help."

*****Please note that my 14-day ban was solely based off of this 1 match and I was banned no less than 3 minutes after the conclusion of it, thus leading me to think that it was an automated ban*****

**UPDATE**: The 0-12 Xin that laned with me did NOT have his account suspended, so if you are having a bad game just make sure you don't make it to 0-13, 0-12 is safe, but 0-13 will get you banned by the automated system that detects intentional feeding.


***Please note that the AP RUNES i forgot to change from my prior match, which was zac bot lane with my same duo, we went duo bruiser bot just like we did this game, and I failed to change them, I WAS NOT TROLLING***

